ConvTranspose3d.missing_message: 3D Transposed Convolution requires framework-specific layer abstractions (e.g. Flax Linen) or complex lax.conv_general_dilated usage.

GatherMM.missing_message: JAX requires vmap/take composition for GatherMM

GetRngState.missing_message: JAX uses stateless PRNG keys, not global RNG state.

Hardshrink.missing_message: HardShrink not direct in JAX NN. Use macro.

Histc.missing_message: JAX histogram logic differs for implicit min/max 0 behavior.

Hspmm.missing_message: Sparse hybrid multiplication not directly supported in JAX core.

IndexReduce.missing_message: Complex index reduction requires .at[].reduce() mapping via plugin.

InitialSeed.missing_message: JAX uses explicit PRNG keys, no global seed state.

InstanceNorm.missing_message: JAX core has no functional instance_norm. Use Flax Linen GroupNorm/LayerNorm.

IntTensor.missing_message: Direct mapping of legacy IntTensor constructor is unsafe. Use jnp.array with dtype=int32.

LongTensor.missing_message: Direct mapping of legacy LongTensor constructor is unsafe. Use jnp.array with dtype=int64.

LuUnpack.missing_message: JAX does not support unpacking raw LU factors. Use jax.scipy.linalg.lu for decomposition.

ModuleDict.missing_message: Use native Python dict for module storage.

OutOfMemoryError.missing_message: Mapping is approximate; JAX throws XlaRuntimeError on OOM.

ParameterDict.missing_message: Use native Python dict for parameter storage.

StdMean.macro_template: (jax.numpy.std({input}, axis={dim}, ddof={correction}, keepdims={keepdim}), jax.numpy.mean({input}, axis={dim}, keepdims={keepdim}))

Unbind.macro_template: [jnp.squeeze(x, axis={dim}) for x in jnp.split({input}, {input}.shape[{dim}], axis={dim})]

UseDeterministicAlgorithms.missing_message: JAX determinism is set via 'jax.config.update'. Transpilation of global config setters is unsafe.

VarMean.macro_template: (jax.numpy.var({x}, axis={axis}, ddof={correction}, keepdims={keepdims}), jax.numpy.mean({x}, axis={axis}, keepdims={keepdims}))

Vjp.macro_template: lambda f, p, c: (lambda out, vjp_fn: (out, vjp_fn(c)))(*jax.vjp(f, *p))
